org.apache.ctakes.ytex.kernel

Class ImputedFeatureEvaluatorImpl.JointDistribution

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ctakes.ytex.kernel.ImputedFeatureEvaluatorImpl.JointDistribution
  • Enclosing class:
    ImputedFeatureEvaluatorImpl

    public static class ImputedFeatureEvaluatorImpl.JointDistribution
extends Object
    joint distribution of concept (x) and class (y). The bins for x and y are predetermined. Typical levels for x are 0/1 (absent/present) and -1/0/1 (negated/not present/affirmed).
    Author:
    vijay

      • merge

        public static ImputedFeatureEvaluatorImpl.JointDistribution merge(List<ImputedFeatureEvaluatorImpl.JointDistribution> jointDistros,
                                                                  Map<String,Set<Long>> yMargin,
                                                                  String xMerge)
        merge joint distributions into a single distribution. For each value of Y, the cells for each X bin, except for the xMerge bin, are the intersection of all the instances in each of the corresponding bins. The xMerge bin gets everything that is leftover.
        Parameters:
        jointDistros - list of joint distribution tables to merge
        yMargin - map of y val - instance id. this could be calculated on the fly, but we have this information already.
        xMerge - the x val that contains everything that doesn't land in any of the other bins.
        Returns:
